    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-01-28T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-01-28T12:00:00-05:00" n="101"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d101">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/3661: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul at Geneva (<persName corresp="#p_GPB1" type="to"
                        >Gilbert</persName>)</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-01-28T12:00:00-05:00"
                            >January 28, 1932—noon</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>30. Your 38, January 26, 9 p.m.<note n="63" xml:id="d101fn63">Not printed.</note>
                    Inform <persName corresp="#p_CVR1">Cecil</persName> as strictly confidential to
                    himself that, before receiving the information contained in <pb facs="0190"
                        n="86" xml:id="pg_86"/> paragraph 5 of your telegram under reference, your
                    Government had instructed the American Ambassador, Tokyo,<note n="64"
                        xml:id="d101fn64">See telegram No. 25, January 27, 2 p.m., <ref
                            target="frus1931-41v01#pg_161">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, Japan, 1931–1941, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, p. 161</ref>.</note> to urge upon the
                    Japanese Foreign Office the importance of the situation at Shanghai in relation
                    to international interests and world peace. Also, that the Secretary of State
                    has noted with interest and appreciation the position which <persName
                        corresp="#p_CVR1">Cecil</persName> has taken, as reported in your paragraph
                    4, in support of the position of the United States in regard to the Manchuria
                    question.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SHL1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
